Name: Shanaya John
Course: CPS842 – Web Search and  Information Retrieval
Vector Space Model Retrieval System

Overview:
This project implements a basic information retrieval (IR) system based on the vector space model.


Program files: 

invert.py: Builds the inverted index from the CACM document collection. Input -> CACM document collection
search.py: Performs document retrieval using cosine similarity. Input -> CACM document collection, dictionary, posting list, common_words
eval.py: Evaluates the IR system by calculating Mean Average Precision (MAP) and Average R-Precision using query.text and qrels.text.
interface.py : an interactive user interface where users can enter queries and see ranked results.

How to Run the Programs:

Step 1: Build the inverted index (invert.py)
    a. Make sure Python 3 and the NLTK Porter Stemmer are installed. (pip install nltk)
    b. Place your document collection file in the same folder as the program, or note its full path.
    c. Run the program:
    d. Follow the instructions displayed in the terminal

Step 2: Interactive interface (interface.py)
    a. Run the program
    b. Input collection, dictionary, posting list path via terminal
    c. Enter the term, when prompted
    d. Enter 'zzend'to end program

Step 3: Evaluate IR System (eval.py)
    a. Make sure query.txt and qrel are in the same folder
    b. Run the program
    Notes: Program may take 1-3 mins to complete execution 
